29328.name: Credit
29328.desc: This currency, used by the Interastral Peace Corporation to settle accounts with its customers, is now widely accepted as the hard currency for space travel.
29328.lore: "People run around fighting and trading for numbers in a terminal, but the truly precious cannot be bought."

67219.name: Horn of Snow
67219.desc: Broken horn of a Frigid Prowler. Can be used for the Ascension of Ice characters.
67219.lore:
The Silvermane Guards would host contests where the winner must take a body part from a monster and bring it back within a set time limit. This cold broken horn must have been a trophy of one such contest.

"Sir Bova, this is no moose horn and is certainly not fit for decoration above the Geomarrow furnace."
comeFrom: Stagnant Shadow: Corridor of Fading Echoes

125435.name: Tracks of Destiny
125435.lore: Your victory is secured by countless failures, and the small steps you have taken led you to the turning point of fate.

409960.name: Traveler's Guide
409960.desc: Experience material for characters. Provides <nobr>20,000</nobr> Character EXP.
409960.lore:
Required reading for world exploration. Press the "Read" button to tune in to an attractive voice in a language you understand, telling you about the legendary encounters of renowned adventurers across different worlds as well as the precious wisdom and knowledge that they have gathered.

"All-new series of the Traveler's Guide, The Chef's Manual to Galactic Cuisine, is now available for purchase."
"For submissions, please connect to synesthesia beacon ERD-23θ to contact an Intelligentsia Guild representative. Method of payment can be arranged to your convenience."

409961.name: Adventure Log
409961.desc: Experience material for characters. Provides <nobr>5000</nobr> Character EXP.
409961.lore:
A neatly organized collection of educational adventure notes containing countless illustrations and texts entailing adventures from beginning to end, as well as valuable information and survival-related techniques.

"Why not just digitize it and save it on a photolith disk? That'd be much more convenient."
"Advanced technology is far more fragile than you'd think when faced with stellar storms and neuron flow eruptions. Besides, I'm sure the author of this book wanted people to read it in the simplest of ways."

409962.name: Travel Encounters
409962.desc: Experience material for characters. Provides <nobr>1000</nobr> Character EXP.
409962.lore:
A travel diary with messy handwriting and random content. It's not of much use to you.

"Dan Heng, hurry up and finish reading it so you can throw it away."

549437.name: Thief's Instinct
549437.desc: A small amount of anti-matter. Crude material used for enhancement.
549437.lore:
A small amount of anti-matter that emanates out of the Voidranger: Reaver like the materialization of its destructive instinct.

"They are all looking forward to the moment of obliteration, when they will be reforged and fused with the entire world."
comeFrom: Dropped by enemies in Divergent Universe

633378.name: Usurper's Scheme
633378.desc: A moderate amount of anti-matter. Normal material used for enhancement.
633378.lore:
A moderate amount of anti-matter that floats around the Voidranger: Distorter. The amount of matter and anti-matter particles has reached a dangerous balance...

"They are all looking forward to the moment of obliteration, when they will be reforged and fused with the entire world."
comeFrom: Antimatter Legion at Equilibrium Level 2 or higher
Dropped by enemies in Divergent Universe

635681.name: Meteoric Bullet
635681.desc: Iron pellets forged for hunting monsters. Each one bears scratches that seem to record the number of prey that perished because of it. Used to level up Traces slightly for The Hunt characters.
635681.lore:
The Armed Archaeologists discovered these iron pellets among various types of monster fossils and bones. Radioactive dating confirmed that they were fired in an era when humanity did not yet exist, and the creatures they shot were the last remnants of a certain monster species.

"Death by old age is no different from death by bullet. The way of the hunter won't lead to a sacred nor sinful end."

717319.name: Conqueror's Will
717319.desc: Condensed anti-matter. Advanced material used for enhancement.
717319.lore:
Highly condensed anti-matter within the body of the Voidranger: Trampler. The moment of obliteration is the trumpet call for civilizations' destruction.

"They are all looking forward to the moment of obliteration, when they will be reforged and fused with the entire world."
comeFrom: Antimatter Legion at Equilibrium Level 4 or higher
Dropped by enemies in Divergent Universe

836267.name: Countertemporal Shot
836267.desc: A spiral bullet forever going against the arrow of time, like a hound eternally chasing the immortal that defies time. Used to level up Traces significantly for The Hunt characters.
836267.lore:
Once the embers of a Lord Ravager, the button to erase a civilization, and the final lament of an ancient behemoth... How many deaths must these materials have gathered to forge such ammunition? And what kind of firearm can propel it into the past? It is the answer to all. It is not a question itself.

"Run. Flee to any moment's interstice. It will always find you, nailing you down in the fabric of fate."

920208.name: Destined Expiration
920208.desc: Embedded in the deceased's brow, piercing through the crevice of matter, this bullet forever resides where its bullet hole should be. Used to level up Traces moderately for The Hunt characters.
920208.lore:
It traversed the winding paths amidst legions of soldiers, pierced through the weakest point of the stoutest helmets, and finally came to rest at the center of the skull of the invincible tyrant, emitting a whisper-like sigh. Its arrival came like a fatal coincidence. Its arrival was akin to an endpoint that all were fated to meet.

"Sometimes, the bullet hole precedes the trajectory."

985668.name: Destroyer's Final Road
985668.lore:
The Leviathan's heart has stopped beating, but its mind lives on despite being trapped in a case. As long as the lid is closed, its mind is simultaneously both alive and dead, driving the engine of destruction.

"Doomsday Beast, a blight made in the Warforge using what's left of a Leviathan and the weeping bones of thousands of the dead. It longs for the destruction of the universe and itself."

ranks.name: My Sword Stirs Starlight
ranks.descHash: When Shifu is on the field, increases March 7th's SPD by <nobr>#1[i]%</nobr>.

ranks.name: Blade Dances on Waves' Fight
ranks.descHash: After "Shifu" uses Basic ATK or Skill to attack an enemy target, March 7th immediately launches a <u>Follow-up ATK</u> and deals Imaginary DMG equal to <nobr>#1[i]%</nobr> of March 7th's ATK to the primary target of this attack. Additionally, triggers the corresponding effect based on "Shifu"'s Path and then gains <nobr>#3[i]</nobr> point(s) of Charge. If there is no primary target available to attack, then she attacks a single random enemy instead. This effect can only trigger once per turn.

ranks.name: Sharp Wit in Martial Might
ranks.descHash:
Skill Lv. +2, up to a maximum of Lv. 15.
Basic ATK Lv. +1, up to a maximum of Lv. 10.

ranks.name: Being Fabulous Never Frights
ranks.descHash: At the start of the turn, regenerates <nobr>#1[i]</nobr> Energy.

ranks.name: Sword Delights, Sugar Blights
ranks.descHash:
Ultimate Lv. +2, up to a maximum of Lv. 15.
Talent Lv. +2, up to a maximum of Lv. 15.

ranks.name: Me, the Best Girl in Sight
ranks.descHash: After using Ultimate, increases the CRIT DMG dealt by the next Enhanced Basic ATK by <nobr>#1[i]%</nobr>.

skills.descHash: Deals Imaginary DMG equal to #1[i]% of March 7th's ATK to a single target enemy and gains #2[i] point(s) of Charge.
skills.name: My Sword Zaps Demons

skills.descHash:
Designates a single ally (excluding this unit) as Shifu and increases Shifu's SPD by #1[f1]%. Only the most recent target of March 7th's Skill is considered as Shifu.


Whenever using Basic ATK or dealing 1 hit of Enhanced Basic ATK's DMG, triggers the corresponding effect if Shifu with the specified Path is present on the field:

Erudition, Destruction, The Hunt: Deals Additional DMG (DMG Type based on Shifu's Combat Type) equal to #2[i]% of March 7th's ATK.

Harmony, Nihility, Preservation, Abundance: Increases the Toughness Reduction of this instance of DMG by #3[i]%.
skills.name: Master, It's Tea Time!

skills.descHash:
Deals Imaginary DMG equal to #1[i]% of March 7th's ATK to a single target enemy.
Increases the initial Hits Per Action of the next Enhanced Basic ATK by #2[i] hits and increase the fixed chance of additionally dealing DMG by #3[i]%.
skills.name: <nobr>March 7th,</nobr> <nobr>the Apex Heroine</nobr>

skills.descHash:
After Shifu uses an attack or Ultimate, March 7th gains up to 1 point of Charge each time.
Upon reaching #1[i] or more points of Charge, March 7th immediately takes action and increases the DMG she deals by #2[i]%. Her Basic ATK gets Enhanced, and her Skill cannot be used. After using Enhanced Basic ATK, consumes #1[i] point(s) of Charge. Charge is capped at #3[i] points.
skills.name: Master, I've Ascended!

skills.descHash: Attacks an enemy, and when the battle starts, reduces their Toughness of the corresponding Type.
skills.name: Attack

skills.descHash:
If March 7th is on the team, she gains 1 point of Charge at the start of the next battle whenever a teammate uses Technique, up to a max of #1[i] point(s).
After using Technique, March 7th regenerates #2[i] Energy when the next battle starts.
skills.name: Feast in One Go

skills.descHash:
Initially, deals #4[i] hits, each causing Imaginary DMG equal to #1[i]% of March 7th's ATK to a single target enemy. Whenever dealing the final hit, there is a #2[i]% fixed chance to deal 1 additional hit of DMG, up to a max of #3[i] additional hit(s). Energy regenerated from using Enhanced Basic ATK does not increase with the number of hits.
Enhanced Basic ATK cannot recover Skill Points.
skills.name: Brows Be Smitten, Heart Be Bitten

embedBonusSkill.descHash: When the battle starts, March 7th's <u>action advances</u> by <nobr>#1[i]%</nobr>.
embedBonusSkill.name: Swan Soar

embedBonusSkill.descHash: March 7th can reduce the Toughness of enemies whose Weakness Type is the same as Shifu's Combat Type. When Breaking Weakness, triggers the Imaginary Weakness Break effect.
embedBonusSkill.name: Filigree

embedBonusSkill.descHash: After using Enhanced Basic ATK, increases Shifu's CRIT DMG by <nobr>#1[i]%</nobr> and Break Effect by <nobr>#2[i]%</nobr>, lasting for <nobr>#3[i]</nobr> turn(s).
embedBonusSkill.name: Tide Tamer

name: March 7th
descHash: March 7th in a Xianzhou-styled outfit. A sword-wielding female martial artist. Learning swordplay from both Yunli and Yanqing, she is eager to create more beautiful memories on the Xianzhou.
